From: CHEN Xuan <chenxuan@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 09:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] default to hipBLASLt as the BLAS backend on gfx110x/gfx1151

Backport of upstream pytorch/pytorch commit 10a5f2ff7c90d8c84938b0e789ab2f4145f90b5d
("[ROCm] Add gfx110X and gfx1151 to preferred hipBLASLt architectures
list (#185375)"), with the ROCm version gate for the added archs lowered
from 71300 to 70200: upstream flips the default only for ROCm >= 7.13,
but openRuyi ships ROCm 7.2.4, where the original bug still reproduces.

On gfx1100 (Radeon RX 7900 XTX) torch defaults to rocBLAS for GEMM, and
the rocBLAS shipped in openRuyi has no fp16 GEMM Tensile solution for
some problem shapes (e.g. an N=10 addmm from a small nn.Linear under
AMP), failing with:

  RuntimeError: CUDA error: HIPBLAS_STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR when calling
  rocblas_gemm_ex(..., rocblas_datatype_f16_r, ...)

fp32/bf16 GEMM and fp16 square matmul are fine; only fp16 GEMM at those
shapes breaks.  hipBLASLt handles every shape, and forcing it
(TORCH_BLAS_PREFER_HIPBLASLT=1) makes the failure disappear.

gfx1100/gfx1101/gfx1151 are all already in getHipblasltSupportedArchs()
(gated at ROCm 6.3 / 7.0 respectively), so the supported-arch check
still passes and the backend is not overridden back to rocBLAS.

Only the CUDAHooks.cpp half of the upstream commit is backported; the
test/test_cuda.py half is left out (distro builds do not run it).
---
 aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff -Naur a/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp b/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp
--- a/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp	2026-07-20 09:19:46.612879802 +0800
+++ b/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp	2026-07-20 09:19:54.144838461 +0800
@@ -554,7 +554,10 @@
     "gfx1200", "gfx1201",
 #endif
 #if ROCM_VERSION >= 70000
-    "gfx950"
+    "gfx950",
+#endif
+#if ROCM_VERSION >= 70200
+    "gfx1100", "gfx1101", "gfx1151"
 #endif
   };
   return archs;
